# Part 2: Implementation Plan

### Phase 0 - Project Scaffold

- Initialize Next.js 15 app with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS
- Install core dependencies: `@copilotkit/react-core`, `@copilotkit/react-ui`, `@copilotkit/runtime`, `@duckdb/duckdb-wasm`, `react-vega`, `vega`, `vega-lite`, `zod`
- Set up the CopilotKit provider in `layout.tsx`
- Create the API route (`app/api/copilotkit/route.ts`) with `BuiltInAgent` + `CopilotRuntime`
- Set up environment variables (OpenAI API key)
- Create a basic `.gitignore`

### Phase 1 - DuckDB WASM Layer

- Create a `useDuckDB` React hook/context that initializes DuckDB WASM client-side
- Implement CSV file upload handling (drag & drop + file picker)
- Register uploaded CSV data into DuckDB with `registerFileText`
- Implement a `runQuery(sql: string)` function that executes SQL and returns typed results
- Auto-detect and store the dataset schema (column names + types) via `DESCRIBE` query
- Test with a sample churn dataset CSV

### Phase 2 - Canvas UI

- Design the canvas layout: sidebar (chat) + main area (canvas)
- Define the `CanvasNode` TypeScript types (insight, chart, hypothesis, experiment, action_item)
- Build a `Canvas` component that renders an array of nodes as cards
- Build individual node card components: `InsightCard`, `ChartCard`, `HypothesisCard`, `ExperimentCard`, `ActionItemCard`
- Implement inline editing on node cards (click to edit title/content)
- Add node positioning (grid layout or free-form drag with a library like `@dnd-kit`)
- Style with Tailwind CSS for a modern, clean look

### Phase 3 - CopilotKit Agent Integration + Shared State

- Set up `useAgent` with the `insight_agent` agent ID
- Define the agent's state schema (nodes array, datasetLoaded, datasetSchema)
- Wire the canvas to render `agent.state.nodes`
- Implement `agent.setState()` calls when the user edits a canvas node
- Create the agent's system prompt (role: data analyst / reasoning partner, knowledge of available tools, instruction to produce reasoning artifacts)
- Configure the `BuiltInAgent` on the API route with the system prompt

### Phase 4 - Frontend Tools (`run_sql_query` + `generate_chart`)

- Register `run_sql_query` via `useFrontendTool`: accepts a SQL string, executes against DuckDB WASM, returns result rows, renders a data preview table
- Register `generate_chart` via `useFrontendTool`: accepts a Vega-Lite spec (JSON), renders the chart via `react-vega`, adds a chart node to the canvas
- Handle tool lifecycle states (inProgress → loading skeleton, complete → rendered result)
- Ensure the agent receives the tool results and can reason over them

### Phase 5 - Reasoning Flow & Agent Prompt Engineering

- Design the agent's reasoning loop: user query → SQL query → data analysis → insight/hypothesis/chart generation → action items
- Craft the system prompt to encourage structured reasoning artifact production
- Ensure the agent creates properly typed canvas nodes (with correct `type`, `title`, `content`, `chartSpec`)
- Test end-to-end flows: "What is the churn rate by plan?" → SQL → chart + insight node
- Implement the "continue reasoning" flow: when a user edits a hypothesis, the agent re-evaluates

### Phase 6 - Thread Persistence & Cross-Session Memory

- Set up LangGraph with a SQLite checkpointer (for development)
- Configure `checkpointer.setup()` to create the persistence tables
- Wire thread IDs into the `useAgent` hook so conversations persist
- Implement a "session list" UI to let users resume previous analysis sessions
- Test page reload → canvas + chat state fully restored
- (Production) Migrate to PostgreSQL-backed persistence

### Phase 7 - Polish & UX

- Loading states and skeletons for DuckDB initialization and queries
- Error handling: invalid SQL, empty results, DuckDB init failure
- Empty state for the canvas (onboarding prompt)
- Responsive layout (sidebar collapsible on mobile)
- Accessibility: ARIA labels on all interactive elements, keyboard navigation
- Dark mode support

### Phase 8 - Arcade Interactive Demo

Use [Arcade](https://www.arcade.software/) to capture an interactive walkthrough of the finished app. Record key flows (uploading a dataset, asking a question, watching the agent produce canvas artifacts, editing a node to trigger re-reasoning, resuming a persisted session). Publish as an embeddable interactive demo for the project landing page or README.

